<dl id="n42020a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n42" href="#n42020a">N42 (VI.B.31)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n42all.htm#n42020a"> 20(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> remit &amp; retain / sins</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Romanists, and their ugly tail, the Ritualistic party in the Episcopal Church, make a great noise about the words of our Saviour in St. John: &ldquo;Whose soever sins ye remit, they are remitted unto them: and whose soever sins ye retain, they are retained&rdquo; (John xx. 23). But again, our Saviour had Himself, once for all, explained what He meant by forgiving and retaining sins &mdash; Matt. xviii. 35; &hellip;. <small> Chiniquy, <a name="CPWC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CPWC"><cite title="source">The Priest The Woman and The Confessional</cite></a> (n.d.) 83</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
